The paper discusses the limitations and practical value of citation-based indicators in measuring the impact of scientific research. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on publication metrics and peer review, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
